          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " He-4(d,d) scattering as polarization standard"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "H.Anklin",
                "J.Jourdan",
                "L.M.Qin",
                "I.Sick",
                "P.Trueb",
                "D.Vetterli",
                "B.Zihirmann",
                "P.A.Schmelzbach"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2SWTBAS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Deptartment fuer Physik und Astronomic."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A gaseous 4-He target was placed in the center of the",
                "scattering chamber.  The cylindrical target had a",
                "diameter of 5 cm, and contained helium of atmospheric",
                "pressure.  Entrance and exit windows, made from 5.8",
                "mg/cm2 Havar foil, were outside the acceptance",
                "defined by the slit system that proceeded the",
                "detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "POLIS"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The polarization of the beam was flipped once a",
                "second through 3 different polarization states:  the",
                "unpolarized state (0), and two tensor- and vector-",
                "polarized states (1,2), the polarization of which was",
                "equal in magnitude, but opposite in sign.",
                "The left-right asymmetry of d-12-C elastic scattering",
                "was continuously measured using a 200 mug/cm2 carbon",
                "target and NaI detectors placed at + and - 50 degrees",
                "scattering angles."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The deuterons and alpha-particles were detected",
                "using stacks of totally depleted Si surface barrier",
                "detectors, with thicknesses ranging from 40 nm to 1 mm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two the detectors were used in polarimeter to m",
                "measure scattered deutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "2SWTBAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDEG"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The thickness of the degraders was known to",
                "<1%.  The effective energy loss of the deuterons was",
                "measured via the energy of the reaction products from",
                "d-He-4 scattering."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " By measuring both energy loss in the thin",
                "detectors, and the total energy, particles could be",
                "cleanly identified, without background."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Faraday cup"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For dead time of the different spin states.  The",
                "dead-time corrections never exceeded 2%."
              ]
            }
          ],
